SSSD ( Open Source Client for Enterprise Identity Management )

Enroll your Linux machine into an Active Directory, FreeIPA or LDAP domain.
Use remote identities, policies and various authentication and authorization
mechanisms to access your computer.

NOTE: Installed under /usr/local intentionally.
      To start automatically set execution bit in /etc/rc.d/rc.sssd and add 
      in /etc/rc.d/rc.local :

      if [ -x /etc/rc.d/rc.sssd ] ; then
          /etc/rc.d/rc.sssd start
      fi

REQUIRES= ding-libs
